(b) Criminal History.—The term "criminal history" means a record of any conviction of, or any adjudication of guilt for, a crime punishable by imprisonment for more than 1 year, under Federal or State law.
(c) Fraudulent Activity.—The term "fraudulent activity" means any act or activity that is fraudulent, deceitful, or designed to deceive, including—
(1) any scheme, plan, or artifice to defraud;
(2) any false statement or misrepresentation with the intent to defraud;
(3) any unauthorized use of a computer or computer network;
(4) any unauthorized access to a computer or computer network;
(5) any disclosure of private information without authorization;
(6) any violation of a privacy law; and
(7) any other act or activity that is intended to deceive or mislead any person.
